Title: A navigation pattern analysis of university department’s websites using a processing mining approach
Author: K. Han, B. Hwang and J. Jeon
Bibliography: [3]K. Han, B. Hwang and J. Jeon, 'A navigation pattern analysis of university department’s websites using a processing mining approach', Innovations in Education and Teaching International, vol. 52, no. 5, pp. 485-498, 2013. Available: 10.1080/14703297.2013.832634.
Brief summary: Case study resulting from increased complexity and growth of university site. While the university site is valuable in providing information for current and prospective students, this growth requires maintaining and upkeep; otherwise, accessability and efficacy declines rapidly. A three step process is used to analyze, interpret, and suggest functional improvements that can be implemented in the future.

Title: A psychometric user experience model based on fuzzy measure approaches
Author: J. Chou
Bibliography: [4]J. Chou, 'A psychometric user experience model based on fuzzy measure approaches', Advanced Engineering Informatics, vol. 38, pp. 794-810, 2018. Available: 10.1016/j.aei.2018.10.010 [Accessed 14 October 2019].
Brief summary: The value of UX in today's markets and products prompts the need for qualitative, quantitative, and objective measures of applicability and effectiveness. Fuzzy measures were implemented to develop a metric through user experience index (UXI).
